## Chapter x. Archives

x.1. Create tar.gz archive:
tar -czvf package.tar.gz dir1 dir2 dir3 file1 file2

x.2. Unpack tar.gz archive:
tar -xvf package.tar.gz

x.3. Custom compression

Different flags stand for different compression:
 -z gzip
 -j bzip2
 -J xz
 -a detect compression program by suffix

-I option defines custom compression program.
Omit present flags for no compression at all

x.4. Standard Output Writing / Standard Input Reading
Use - instead of archive name, e.g.:
tar -czvf - directory1
tar -xvf -

